content:
Enhance your Decision Table Logic by using the Does Not Match and Contains operators.

You can use these operators when you configure the Column Logic in a decision table. The Does Not Match operator retrieves an output if the query value doesn’t contain the exact value or a subset of the value in the table’s input cell. The Contains operator retrieves an output if the input cell value is an exact match or subset of the value that you look up.

This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions for Industries clouds where Business Rules Engine is enabled.
title: Enhance Decision Table Logic with Does Not Match and Contains Operators
